<div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>

<td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. See its nomination <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sound_candidates/The_Four_Seasons" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sound candidates/The Four Seasons">here</a>.<br/><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the Spanish language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/es:Wikipedia:Recursos_destacados" title="w:es:Wikipedia:Recursos destacados">Recursos destacados</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>
</tr>

<td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td>This file was selected as the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Media_of_the_day" title="Commons:Media of the day">media of the day</a></b> for 27 March 2010. It was captioned as follows:
<div style="direction:ltr;">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div>
</div>
<div class="tpl-hidden mw-collapsible mw-collapsed">
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r922807911">.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden{clear:both}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden>.mw-collapsible-toggle{float:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden::before{display:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{padding-left:20px;background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/10/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_action_arrow.png");background-position:left 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/41/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_right_arrow.png")}.mw-parser-output [dir=rtl] .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_left_arrow.png")}</style>
<div class="mw-collapsible-toggle" style="font-weight:bold; ; text-align:start; float:none;font-size:smaller;margin-left:1em"><span class="tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle skin-invert"></span><span class="tpl-hidden-headertext">Other languages</span></div>

<div class="description als" dir="ltr" lang="als"><span class="language als" title="Alemannic"><b>Alemannisch: </b></span> Styck vum <i>Fryhling</i> vum <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description cs" dir="ltr" lang="cs"><span class="language cs" title="Czech"><b>Čeština: </b></span> Skladba 1 (Allegro) z <i>Jara</i> od Antonia Vivaldiho</div><div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div><div class="description hu" dir="ltr" lang="hu"><span class="language hu" title="Hungarian"><b>Magyar: </b></span> <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a>: Tavasz, 1. tétel (Allegro)</div><div class="description it" dir="ltr" lang="it"><span class="language it" title="Italian"><b>Italiano: </b></span> Primo movimento (Allegro) della <i>Primavera</i> di <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description lb" dir="ltr" lang="lb"><span class="language lb" title="Luxembourgish"><b>Lëtzebuergesch: </b></span> 1. <div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>
</tr>
<tr>

<td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td>This file was selected as the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Media_of_the_day" title="Commons:Media of the day">media of the day</a></b> for 27 March 2010. It was captioned as follows:
<div style="direction:ltr;">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div>
</div>
<div class="tpl-hidden mw-collapsible mw-collapsed">
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r922807911">.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden{clear:both}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden>.mw-collapsible-toggle{float:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden::before{display:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{padding-left:20px;background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/10/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_action_arrow.png");background-position:left 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/41/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_right_arrow.png")}.mw-parser-output [dir=rtl] .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_left_arrow.png")}</style>
<div class="mw-collapsible-toggle" style="font-weight:bold; ; text-align:start; float:none;font-size:smaller;margin-left:1em"><span class="tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle skin-invert"></span><span class="tpl-hidden-headertext">Other languages</span></div>

<div class="description als" dir="ltr" lang="als"><span class="language als" title="Alemannic"><b>Alemannisch: </b></span> Styck vum <i>Fryhling</i> vum <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description cs" dir="ltr" lang="cs"><span class="language cs" title="Czech"><b>Čeština: </b></span> Skladba 1 (Allegro) z <i>Jara</i> od Antonia Vivaldiho</div><div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div><div class="description hu" dir="ltr" lang="hu"><span class="language hu" title="Hungarian"><b>Magyar: </b></span> <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a>: Tavasz, 1. tétel (Allegro)</div><div class="description it" dir="ltr" lang="it"><span class="language it" title="Italian"><b>Italiano: </b></span> Primo movimento (Allegro) della <i>Primavera</i> di <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description lb" dir="ltr" lang="lb"><span class="language lb" title="Luxembourgish"><b>Lëtzebuergesch: </b></span> 1. <div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>
</tr>

<td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td>This file was selected as the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Media_of_the_day" title="Commons:Media of the day">media of the day</a></b> for 27 March 2010. It was captioned as follows:
<div style="direction:ltr;">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div>
</div>
<div class="tpl-hidden mw-collapsible mw-collapsed">
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r922807911">.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden{clear:both}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden>.mw-collapsible-toggle{float:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden::before{display:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{padding-left:20px;background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/10/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_action_arrow.png");background-position:left 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/41/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_right_arrow.png")}.mw-parser-output [dir=rtl] .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_left_arrow.png")}</style>
<div class="mw-collapsible-toggle" style="font-weight:bold; ; text-align:start; float:none;font-size:smaller;margin-left:1em"><span class="tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle skin-invert"></span><span class="tpl-hidden-headertext">Other languages</span></div>

<div class="description als" dir="ltr" lang="als"><span class="language als" title="Alemannic"><b>Alemannisch: </b></span> Styck vum <i>Fryhling</i> vum <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description cs" dir="ltr" lang="cs"><span class="language cs" title="Czech"><b>Čeština: </b></span> Skladba 1 (Allegro) z <i>Jara</i> od Antonia Vivaldiho</div><div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div><div class="description hu" dir="ltr" lang="hu"><span class="language hu" title="Hungarian"><b>Magyar: </b></span> <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a>: Tavasz, 1. tétel (Allegro)</div><div class="description it" dir="ltr" lang="it"><span class="language it" title="Italian"><b>Italiano: </b></span> Primo movimento (Allegro) della <i>Primavera</i> di <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description lb" dir="ltr" lang="lb"><span class="language lb" title="Luxembourgish"><b>Lëtzebuergesch: </b></span> 1. <div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>
</tr>

<th scope="row">Location of birth/death</th>
<td class="halfwidth" id="fileinfotpl_creator_birthloc_value">

<td>This file was selected as the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Media_of_the_day" title="Commons:Media of the day">media of the day</a></b> for 27 March 2010. It was captioned as follows:
<div style="direction:ltr;">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div>

<div class="mw-collapsible-toggle" style="font-weight:bold; ; text-align:start; float:none;font-size:smaller;margin-left:1em"><span class="tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle skin-invert"></span><span class="tpl-hidden-headertext">Other languages</span></div>
<div class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-weight:normal; color: inherit;; text-align:start;">
<div class="description als" dir="ltr" lang="als"><span class="language als" title="Alemannic"><b>Alemannisch: </b></span> Styck vum <i>Fryhling</i> vum <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description cs" dir="ltr" lang="cs"><span class="language cs" title="Czech"><b>Čeština: </b></span> Skladba 1 (Allegro) z <i>Jara</i> od Antonia Vivaldiho</div><div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div><div class="description hu" dir="ltr" lang="hu"><span class="language hu" title="Hungarian"><b>Magyar: </b></span> <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a>: Tavasz, 1. tétel (Allegro)</div><div class="description it" dir="ltr" lang="it"><span class="language it" title="Italian"><b>Italiano: </b></span> Primo movimento (Allegro) della <i>Primavera</i> di <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description lb" dir="ltr" lang="lb"><span class="language lb" title="Luxembourgish"><b>Lëtzebuergesch: </b></span> 1. <div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>
</tr>

<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>

<td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td>This file was selected as the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Media_of_the_day" title="Commons:Media of the day">media of the day</a></b> for 27 March 2010. It was captioned as follows:
<div style="direction:ltr;">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div>
</div>
<div class="tpl-hidden mw-collapsible mw-collapsed">
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r922807911">.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden{clear:both}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden>.mw-collapsible-toggle{float:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden::before{display:none}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{padding-left:20px;background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/10/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_action_arrow.png");background-position:left 50%;background-repeat:no-repeat}.mw-parser-output .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/41/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_right_arrow.png")}.mw-parser-output [dir=rtl] .tpl-hidden.mw-made-collapsible.mw-collapsed>.mw-collapsible-toggle>.tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle{background-image:url("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/MediaWiki_Vector_skin_left_arrow.png")}</style>
<div class="mw-collapsible-toggle" style="font-weight:bold; ; text-align:start; float:none;font-size:smaller;margin-left:1em"><span class="tpl-hidden-arrowtoggle skin-invert"></span><span class="tpl-hidden-headertext">Other languages</span></div>

<div class="description als" dir="ltr" lang="als"><span class="language als" title="Alemannic"><b>Alemannisch: </b></span> Styck vum <i>Fryhling</i> vum <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description cs" dir="ltr" lang="cs"><span class="language cs" title="Czech"><b>Čeština: </b></span> Skladba 1 (Allegro) z <i>Jara</i> od Antonia Vivaldiho</div><div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div><div class="description hu" dir="ltr" lang="hu"><span class="language hu" title="Hungarian"><b>Magyar: </b></span> <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a>: Tavasz, 1. tétel (Allegro)</div><div class="description it" dir="ltr" lang="it"><span class="language it" title="Italian"><b>Italiano: </b></span> Primo movimento (Allegro) della <i>Primavera</i> di <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description lb" dir="ltr" lang="lb"><span class="language lb" title="Luxembourgish"><b>Lëtzebuergesch: </b></span> 1. <td style="width:64px; text-align:center;"><span typeof="mw:File"><span title="Media of the day"><img alt="Media of the day" class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="400" data-file-width="400" decoding="async" height="45" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Motd-logo_02.svg/45px-Motd-logo_02.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Motd-logo_02.svg/68px-Motd-logo_02.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Motd-logo_02.svg/90px-Motd-logo_02.svg.png 2x" width="45"/></span></span>

<td>This file was selected as the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Media_of_the_day" title="Commons:Media of the day">media of the day</a></b> for 27 March 2010. It was captioned as follows:
<div style="direction:ltr;">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div>

John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div>,

<div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>
</tr>
<tr>

<td>

<div id="shared-image-desc"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" dir="ltr" lang="en"><div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Summary">Summary</h2></div>
<div class="hproduct commons-file-information-table">
<table class="fileinfotpl-type-information vevent" dir="ltr">
<tbody><tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_src" lang="en">Source</td>
<td>
<span class="int-own-work" lang="en">Own work</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_aut" lang="en">Author</td>
<td>

<th colspan="4"><span class="fn" id="creator"><bdi><a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi"><span title="Italian composer and violinist (1678-1741)">Antonio Vivaldi</span></a>
</bdi></span> (1678–1741) <span class="skin-invert" typeof="mw:File"><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Creator:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Creator:Antonio Vivaldi"><img class="mw-file-element" <td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_date" lang="en">Date</td>
<td lang="en">
composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>

<td style="width:64px; text-align:center;"><span typeof="mw:File"><span title="Media of the day"><img alt="Media of the day" class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="400" data-file-width="400" decoding="async" height="45" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Motd-logo_02.svg/45px-Motd-logo_02.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Motd-logo_02.svg/68px-Motd-logo_02.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Motd-logo_02.svg/90px-Motd-logo_02.svg.png 2x" width="45"/></span></span>

<td>This file was selected as the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Media_of_the_day" title="Commons:Media of the day">media of the day</a></b> for 27 March 2010. It was captioned as follows:
<div style="direction:ltr;">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Movement 1 (Allegro) of <i>Spring</i> by Antonio Vivaldi</div>

<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>

<td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. <td class="fileinfo-paramfield" id="fileinfotpl_desc" lang="en">Description<span class="summary fn" style="display:none">Vivaldi - Four Seasons 1 Spring mvt 1 Allegro - John Harrison violin.oga</span></td>
<td class="description">
<div class="description en" dir="ltr" lang="en"><span class="language en" title="English"><b>English: </b></span> Concerto No. 1 in E major, Op. 8, RV 269, "La primavera" (Spring) — Movement 1: Allegro from <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:The_Four_Seasons_(Vivaldi)" title="w:en:The Four Seasons (Vivaldi)">The Four Seasons</a> by <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Antonio_Vivaldi" title="w:en:Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a><br/>
<p><small>Live, Unedited performance — 3m:35.280s</small><br/>
Wiedemann Recital Hall, <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wichita_State_University" title="w:Wichita State University">Wichita State University</a><br/>
</p>
John Harrison — Violin / Robert Turizziani — Conductor / Wichita State University Chamber Players</div></td>
</tr>,

composed 1723 and published in 1725, performed on 2000-02-06</td>

<td rowspan="2" style="width:30px;text-align:center;">
<p><span typeof="mw:File"><span title="Wikipedia"><img alt="Wikipedia" class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="94" data-file-width="103" decoding="async" height="27" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Wikipedia-logo-v2.svg/30px-Wikipedia-logo-v2.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Wikipedia-logo-v2.svg/45px-Wikipedia-logo-v2.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Wikipedia-logo-v2.svg/60px-Wikipedia-logo-v2.svg.png 2x" width="30"/></span></span>

<td>
<table class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed skin-invert" style="clear:both;margin:2px auto;background:#FAF5E6;color:#222;border:1px solid #FAF5E6;padding:1px;width:100%">
<tbody><tr>
<th scope="col" style="font-size:100%;background:#E5D4A1;border:none;color:#000;padding:0 .2em;text-align:center">Wikipedia
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td class="mw-collapsible-content" style="font-size:100%;border:none;padding:0;text-align:left"><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="443" data-file-width="466" decoding="async" height="19" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/20px-Cscr-featured.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/30px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Cscr-featured.svg/40px-Cscr-featured.svg.png 2x" width="20"/></span></span><span typeof="mw:File"><span><img class="mw-file-element" data-file-height="96" data-file-width="128" decoding="async" height="12" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/16px-Sound-icon.svg.png" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/24px-Sound-icon.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Sound-icon.svg/32px-Sound-icon.svg.png 2x" width="16"/></span></span> This is a <b>featured sound</b> on the English language Wikipedia (<a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Wikipedia:Featured_sounds" title="w:en:Wikipedia:Featured sounds">Featured sounds</a>) and is considered one of the finest sound files. Saz (Allegro) vum <i>Fréijoer</i> vum <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description mk" dir="ltr" lang="mk"><span class="language mk" title="Macedonian"><b>Македонски: </b></span> Став 1 (Алегро) од „Пролет“ („<a class="extiw" href="https://mk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%A7%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%B8%D1%80%D0%B8_%D0%B3%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B8%D1%88%D0%BD%D0%B8_%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B8%D1%9A%D0%B0" title="mk:Четири годишни времиња">Четири годишни времиња</a>“) од <a class="extiw" href="https://mk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%90%D0%BD%D1%82%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%BE_%D0%92%D0%B8%D0%B2%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B4%D0%B8" title="mk:Антонио Вивалди">Антонио Вивалди</a></div><div class="description pl" dir="ltr" lang="pl"><span class="language pl" title="Polish"><b>Polski: </b></span> <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antonio Vivaldi</a> - <i>Wiosna</i> ze zbioru <i>Cztery pory roku</i> (cz. I <i>Allegro</i>)</div><div class="description scn" dir="ltr" lang="scn"><span class="language scn" title="Sicilian"><b>Sicilianu: </b></span> Primu muvimentu (Allegru) dâ <i>Primavera</i> d'<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Vivaldi" title="Antonio Vivaldi">Antoniu Vivaldi</a></div><div class="description zh-hant" dir="ltr" lang="zh-hant"><span class="language zh-hant" title="Traditional Chinese"><b>中文（繁體）：</b></span><a class="extiw" href="https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%AE%89%E6%9D%B1%E5%B0%BC%E5%A5%A7%C2%B7%E7%B6%AD%E7%93%A6%E7%88%BE%E7%AC%AC" title="zh:安東尼奧·維瓦爾第">安東尼奧·維瓦爾第</a>的作品《<a class="extiw" href="https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%9B%9B%E5%AD%A3_(%E7%B6%AD%E7%93%A6%E7%88%BE%E7%AC%AC)" title="zh:四季 (維瓦爾第)">四季</a>》之《春》，第一樂章：快板</div>
